  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "The kubernetes middlware assumes all domains with 5 segments before the zone are of _port._protocol.service.namespace.type.zone format. it tests this assumption even for non-SRV requests, despite non-SRV having no such concept, and returns an SRVFAIL (not NXDOMAIN) when the check fails. as a consequence, the kubernetes search domains are broken as a lookup may accidentally match the 5-segment check.\r\n\r\nas a simple example, running `apk update` in an alpine-based container breaks, as the `dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org` lookup becomes `dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org.default.svc.$ZONE`, matches the 5-segment check, and produces an error like\r\n`23/Jan/2017:13:32:37 +0000 [ERROR 0 dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org.default.svc.$ZONE. A] srv port must start with an underscore or be a wildcard`. because this is a srvfail rather than nxdomain, the search stops there and the domain lookup fails.",
